args: Whoa, this place is HUGE!\nI really get the whole room to myself?
Of course. I pray it will keep you in comfort\nuntil we are prepared to infiltrate the Jail.
Aw, thanks! Don't know that we'll have\nmuch time to relax, though. There's a ton\nwe have to do to get ready.
Then to the extent I may be of assistance,\ndo not hesitate to call upon me.
I gather that your world is quite different\nfrom our own, and am certain your mind\nmust be aboil with questions.

It totally is! Okay, so one thing's been 
driving me crazy is that I always stock
up on medicine and supplies before a Jail
run—just to be safe, you know?
But Sophie can't get online to order stuff,\nand your big medieval castle doesn't seem\nto have a pharmacy or anything.
On...line? Er, I do not fully ken the extent\nof your problem, but it seems you seek\nmedicine with which to treat wounds?
Exactly! So is that the sorta thing I could\nbuy if I go to a big enough town here?
Well, yes—but it would be faster to simply\nforage for healing herbs on your own.
You're telling me you guys have medicine\nthat just...grows out of the ground?!
Er...yes? I take it you do not?
I mean, I guess we sort of do? But no\nnormal person wanders into the woods\nto pick it for themselves.
Hmm. Perhaps the differences between\nour worlds are even more fundamental\nthan I first imagined.

In any case, we have skilled herbalists
and apothecaries here at the Halidom,
so I shall have one assist you in gathering
whatever you require.
That'd be a huge help, Elly. Thanks!

It's my pleasure—and again, do not
hesitate to ask if there is aught else I
might do. Until then, I pray you relax
and enjoy your stay here to the utmost.
Aw, Elly's so nice—and so on top of it!
Which means it'd be an insult to NOT\nkick back and enjoy this sweet room!
...Ugh, nope nope nope. This room is way\ntoo big. Besides, I think I'm going through\nsocial media withdrawal.
I guess life as normal was never really\nan option here, so...what now?
...And that's why I'm here.\nSorry, Elly. I hope you don't mind\nme hanging out with you.
There is no need for apologies; if my\ncompany will suffice, I am happy for us\nto spend our hours together.
Sweet! Okay, so I'm super curious to\nlearn more about you. I mean, if you're\ncool with that, of course.
Well, yeah! We're friends now, so I wanna\nget to know you. Is that not something\nyou guys do here?
No, of course it is. I merely didn't...\nYes, anyway, I am happy to share.\nPerhaps I ought to start at the beginning.
My name is Elisanne, and I am a Paladyn\nof the Ilian Church.
Neat! Think you could explain some more?
The Ilian Church is an organization that\nholds great religious sway in this land\nand works tirelessly to preserve order.
We Paladyns are one of the means by\nwhich it does so; we are tasked with\nprotecting the Church's priests and such.
Oh, so you're like a holy bodyguard?\nThat is so cool! I can totally see it.
We've actually got a girl with a similar\nvibe in the Phantom Thieves.
She's straight-laced, but really nice and\nsuper tough. Her code name's Queen.
Alas, I fear I do not deserve to be placed\nin such esteemed company, for I have\nfailed to live up to the honor of my office.

Recent years have seen a rift develop
between my beliefs and the Church's
teachings, and I find myself...struggling.
Doubting, even.
I don't think going through a rough patch\nis anything to be ashamed of, though.

Okay, so back when I started out as a
model, I didn't really give it much thought.
I just showed up, struck a few rad poses,
and figured that was that.
But, of course, that was super naive of me.\nSoon enough, I hit a wall. Doubted myself,\nstruggled to continue, all of it.
But I made it through. And because I did,\nI gained the strength to totally recommit to\nmy career as a model.
So don't ever feel bad for having doubts!\nThey're just a sign of how you're thinking\nand growing as a person, you know?
...Thank you, Panther. Your words have\nbrought me great comfort this day.
You are a remarkable woman; very few\nhave the poise to turn their greatest\nstruggles into a strength.
Oh stop, you're gonna make me blush!

I might have made it sound cool, but all
that really happened was I realized how 
lame it was to not be committing myself
to my modeling.
I am most unfamiliar with the art world,\nand did not understand the resolve required\nof those who sit for portraits.

Huh? Sorry, not that kind of model... Not
after that one time. I'm talking about
photos. Magazines. Editorial content,
y'know?
...Which I can see from your face is not\nstuff that you have around here. Well then,\nlet me tell you a bit about my world now!
I am most eager to hear any stories\nyou are willing to share.
Well, I hope your evening's free,\nbecause I'm ready to talk all night!
